Chocolate cake. Ingredients:eggs - 2 pcs, flour - 2 cups, sugar - 2 cups, soda - 1.5 tsp, baking powder - 1.5 tsp, Milk - 1 cup, oil - 0.5 cups, vanilla sugar - 1 sachet, boiling water - 1 cup, cocoa - 5 tbsp. Step-by-step preparation: Beat the eggs with sugar with a mixer until a small foam forms. Add room temperature milk and oil to the mixture. In a separate bowl, mix the following ingredients: sifted flour, baking powder, baking soda, cocoa and vanilla sugar. Gradually add the dry ingredients to the egg and butter mixture, while continuing to whisk together. Add a glass of boiling water to the finished batter and immediately mix everything thoroughly. Pour the batter into the baking tin. Bake for about 50 minutes at 180Â°C.
